    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Midgame Strategy — Controlling the Board",
    "description": "Master Scrabble midgame strategy: board control, balancing offense and defense, lane management, and positioning for endgame.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/midgame-strategy" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "When does the midgame start in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The midgame typically begins around turns 4-5, when the board has enough tiles to create multiple scoring lanes and the bag still has 40-60 tiles. It ends when the bag has fewer than 15 tiles and endgame calculation begins." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you control the board in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Board control means choosing plays that create opportunities for yourself while limiting your opponent's options. This includes: playing in areas where you can extend on future turns, blocking lanes to premium squares when ahead, and keeping the board shape favorable for your tile strengths." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should you open or close the board in Scrabble midgame?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "It depends on your position. When ahead, close the board to protect your lead. When behind or holding a bingo-ready rack, open the board to create scoring opportunities. When even, play situationally — open when you have strong tiles, close when you don't." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Strategy</span>
