      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Play toward hot quadrants:</span> Identify which board areas still have accessible premium squares. Focus your plays there — don't waste turns in dead zones scoring 8 points.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Match your style to your position:</span> Ahead → close. Behind → open. Even → read your rack strength. Don't play one style regardless of the game state.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Avoid setups unless you hold the key tile:</span> Setup plays only work if you'll be the one to exploit the lane. If the key tile is common (S, E, R), assume your opponent has it too.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Start closing 5 turns before bag empties:</span> Don't wait until the endgame to play defensively. Gradual closing is harder to punish than sudden board shutdown.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Dump problem tiles in the transition:</span> Q, V, W, and duplicate vowels become stuck-tile liabilities. Get them off your rack while exchanges are still possible.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

